      "contentBlocks": [
        "Liberal Studies provides a broad academic program encouraging academic excellence, diversity, community, and collaboration.",
        "The Liberal Studies program is an interdisciplinary major, which encompasses a wide variety of areas of knowledge in a multidisciplinary curriculum. It is a major designed for students who either (i) intend on becoming elementary or special education teachers in California, or (ii) who have an interest in an interdisciplinary course of study. The Liberal Studies major is a California Commission on Teacher Credentialing-approved subject matter program. The curriculum provides excellent preparation for careers in teaching, government service, community service, counseling, librarianship, and public health.",
        "There are 2 tracks in the Liberal Studies Program: general & pre-credential tracks",
        "Temporary Faculty Eligible to Apply for 3-year Appointment.",
        "CSET Waiver Form for Sac State Credential Program",
        "CSET Waiver Form for Non-Sac State Credential Programs",
        "Email unofficial transcripts from all colleges and universities attended to Kristen Anderegg . Evaluations may take up to 2 business weeks.",
        "Liberal Studies majors are required to meet with a Liberal Studies advisor EVERY semester until graduation.",
        "Due to limited availability, walk-in advising is not available . All advising appointments must be scheduled in advance. If you are not enrolled at Sac State and would like to see an advisor, please contact us at libssis-office@csus.edu. For current Sac State students, see the instructions below:",
        "Holds are displayed in your Student Center. Contact the corresponding campus department for assistance. A video tutorial for reviewing holds is available in the Sac State Student YouTube channel.",
        "If you have a Liberal Studies advising hold on your account but have changed your major, contact our office and include your student ID number.",
        "The Liberal Studies Roadmap provides a pathway to help students complete the degree quickly and efficiently.",
        "The Liberal Studies Learning Objectives help students know what is expected from their coursework.",
        "AAC&U's Liberal Education and America's Promise (LEAP) VALUE rubrics: The rubrics articulate fundamental criteria for each learning outcome, with performance descriptors demonstrating progressively more sophisticated levels of attainment. The rubrics are intended for institutional-level use in evaluating and discussing student learning, not for grading. The core expectations articulated in all 16 of the VALUE rubrics can and should be translated into the language of individual campuses, disciplines, and even courses. The utility of the VALUE rubrics is to position learning at all undergraduate levels within a basic framework of expectations such that evidence of learning can by shared nationally through a common dialog and understanding of student success. Click here for the rubrics.",
        "Liberal Studies Office Lassen Hall, Room 2008 Monday \u2013 Friday, 8 a.m. \u2013 5 p.m.",
        "Phone: (916) 278-6342 libssis-office@csus.edu"
      ],
